The paper is about multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL), which is a subfield of machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI). The paper focuses on decentralized batch MARL with networked agents, which involves both learning and communication among agents. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the theoretical foundation of MARL, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper considers two settings, where agents either collaborate or compete, which are related to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), respectively.
